# Academic Search AI - Walkthrough

## Objectives Accomplished
- ✅ **Unpacked and Cloned**: Successfully duplicated the `ResearchProAI_Template` into a new `ScienceResearchAI` instance.
- ✅ **Academic Search Integration**: Implemented a restricted internet search using `duckduckgo-search` (DDGS). The search is strictly limited to academic and scientific domains (`.edu`, `.gov`, `arxiv.org`, `nature.com`, `ncbi.nlm.nih.gov`).
- ✅ **Enhanced RAG Pipeline**: Modified [generate_report.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/kaggle-arena/ScienceResearchAI/ResearchProAI_Template/src/generate_report.py) to combine local knowledge base context with real-time academic web search results.
- ✅ **Infrastructure Fixes**: Resolved critical `SyntaxError` (unterminated string literals) and `NameError` (undefined variables in list comprehensions) in the original template's [ingest.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/kaggle-arena/ScienceResearchAI/ResearchProAI_Template/src/ingest.py) and [generate_report.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/kaggle-arena/ScienceResearchAI/ResearchProAI_Template/src/generate_report.py).
- ✅ **Verification**: Validated the system with a query on "latest research on CRISPR", which produced a structured scientific report with accurate citations.

## Changes Made

### [generate_report.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/kaggle-arena/ScienceResearchAI/ResearchProAI_Template/src/generate_report.py)
- Integrated `DDGS` for web search.
